Output shows:

    0.0.0.0 or default â†’ your gateway IP (e.g., 192.168.1.1).

âš¡ Key Takeaways

    Traceroute maps the path packets take.

    Useful for troubleshooting network issues (latency, packet loss, misconfigured gateway).

    Works best when DNS resolution is successful â€” otherwise, use IP directly.

    Combined with ping, itâ€™s one of the most important Linux network troubleshooting tools.

